 that our current cosmological understanding of gradual mass +\ndust buildup of galaxies with cosmic time is largely accurate to describe the\n~0.7-1.5 Gyr age window of the Universe. The abundance of a large population of\nUV faint dust-poor systems may point to a dominance of low-mass galaxies at z>6\nplaying a vital role in cosmic reionization.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Jul 2022 02:33:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 30 Jul 2022 02:15:23 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 14 Mar 2023 07:44:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-03"}
