 its magnitude by -1.27 %. For corresponding\nhydrides of superheavy flerovium, the electronic structures are quite similar.\nInterestingly, the QED contribution to the reaction energy is of quite similar\nmagnitude (0.35 kcal/mol), whereas the relative change is significantly smaller\n(-0.50 %). This curious observation can be explained by the faster increase of\nnegative vacuum polarization over positive electron self-energy contributions\nas a function of nuclear charge.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Jul 2022 14:14:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-09"}
